                     <decoDesc>
                         <summary>The full-page miniatures, not arranged in chronological order, are painted in the <term key="FirstGondarineStyle" ana="#FirstGondarineStyle">First Gondarine Style</term>. 
                             The pigments, which  are typical for the period, have often flaked off at the edges of the parchment. In some scenes the background is painted whereas in others
                         the parchment is used for the ground.</summary>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                           <locus target="#5v">Fol. 5v</locus>
                           <desc>
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5687Joachim">Joachim</persName>, identified by the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢያቂም</foreign>, and 
                               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1948Anne">Anne</persName>, identified by the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐና፡</foreign>, who
                               carries <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>, identified by the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም</foreign>, 
                               on her back.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                           <locus target="#6v">Fol. 6v</locus>
                            <desc> A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1002Annunciation">Annunciation</ref>.
                               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName>, identified by the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብርኤል</foreign>, performs a <term key="gestureblessing" ana="#gestureblessing">gesture of speech</term>.
                               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>, identified by the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም</foreign>, is spinning.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                           <locus target="#7v">Fol. 7v</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1036MercyCovenant">Covenant of Mercy</ref>.
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> holds the hand of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> while sitting beside her.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                           <locus target="#8v">Fol. 8v</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1064Visitation">Visitation</ref> in which
                               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>, identified by the caption  <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም</foreign>
                               and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3725Elizabet">ʾElsābeṭ</persName>, identified by the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኤልሳቤጥ፡ መጥምቅ፡</foreign>, embrace each other.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                           <locus target="#9v">Fol. 9v</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1025NativityJesus">Nativity of Jesus</ref>:
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> is lying between <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>
                                and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5764Joseph">Joseph</persName>, identified by a caption as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዮሴፍ</foreign>. There are two
                            <term key="angel" ana="#angel">angels</term> in the background. Whereas a donkey, identified by the caption
                                <foreign xml:lang="gez">አድግ</foreign> and an ox, identified by a hardly readable caption, on the ground.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ወለደት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ መርያም፡ ለእግዚእነ፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                           <locus target="#10v">Fol. 10v</locus>
                            <desc>An <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> showing <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> using
                                a <term key="spear" ana="#spear"/> to kill the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/>.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7">
                           <locus target="#11r">Fol. 11r</locus>
                           <desc>A typical rendering of the 
                               <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> is holding
                               <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName>. Two <term key="angel" ana="#angel">angels</term> are depicted in the background.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8">
                           <locus target="#12r">Fol. 12r</locus>
                           <desc>A miniature of the
                              <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1016Flight">Flight into Egypt</ref>. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> is riding a donkey and
                               feeding the infant <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> who suckles on her breast. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8417Salome">Salome</persName>,
                               identified by a caption as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰሎሜ</foreign> stands on the left holding a gourge and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5764Joseph">Joseph</persName>,
                               identified by a caption as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዮሴፍ</foreign> on the right.
                           </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ነገደት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ውስተ፡ ደብረ፡ ቍስቋም፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9">
                           <locus target="#13v">Fol. 13v</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature showing an episode of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1058DormitionMary">Dormition of Mary</ref>.
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> is shown in prayer and
                            is surrounded by the Twelve Apostles.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10">
                           <locus target="#14r">Fol. 14r</locus>
                            <desc>A second episode from the  <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1058DormitionMary">Dormition of Mary</ref>.
                                The Apostles carry the shrouded body of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> on a bed for burial. 
                                The miniature also features the repentant Jewish priest Jephonias who has lost his hand in the attempt to topple the bed.
                               </desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ገነዝዋ፡ ሐዋርየት፡ <gap reason="illegible"/> ማርያም፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11">
                           <locus target="#15r">Fol. 15r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1037AscensionMary">Assumption of Mary</ref>. The caption reads:
                                How the <term key="angel" ana="#angel">angels</term> brought <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> to Heaven.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ አዕረግዋ፡ መላእክት፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12">
                           <locus target="#16r">Fol. 16r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1015Flagellation">Flagellation of Jesus</ref>. 
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> is bound to a pillar while two soldiers flog him.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ አሰርዎ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ድኅሪተ፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d13">
                           <locus target="#17r">Fol. 17r</locus>
                            <desc> A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1065RoadtoCalvary">Road to Calvary</ref>.
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> is carrying the <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>. Two persons with whips walk behind him.
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> is standing to the left.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ አድር<gap reason="illegible"/> ለእግዚእነ፡ መስቀለ፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d14">
                           <locus target="#18r">Fol. 18r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the  <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1023Mocking">Mocking of Jesus</ref>.
                                Two <term key="guard" ana="#guard">guards</term> stand behind him.
                               The eyes of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> are blindfolded.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ገልበ፡ በዎ፡ ገጾ፡ ለእግዚእነ</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d15">
                           <locus target="#19r">Fol. 19r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref> with the <term key="deadjesus" ana="#deadjesus"/> on the 
                                <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>, to the left, and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5695John">John</persName>, to the right,
                                perform a <term key="gesturegrief" ana="#gesturegrief"/>.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ሰቀልዎ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d16">
                           <locus target="#20r">Fol. 20r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature showing the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1033Ascension">Ascension of Jesus</ref>.
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> has outspread arms. The <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11430Apostles">Twelve Apostles</persName> are smaller in size.
                                </desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ሥዕለ፡ ዕርገቱ፡ ለእግዚእነ</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d17">
                           <locus target="#21r">Fol. 21r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1055ManofSorrows">Man of Sorrows</ref>.
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> is at the centre of the composition, his palms turned upwards in front of his chest. 
                                A crown of thorns is placed on his head.
                                Two <term key="guard" ana="#guard">guards</term> hold axes in one hand and press spikes into his head with the other. 
                                </desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d18">
                           <locus target="#22r">Fol. 22r</locus>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1008Descent">Descent into Hell</ref>.
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> pulls up Adam with his right hand and Eve with his left. 
                                There is a banner behind him.</desc>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ሥዕለ፡ ትንሣኤሁ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡</q>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d19">
                           <locus target="#23r">Fol. 23r</locus>
                            <desc>
                              <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>:
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3934Ewostate">ʾEwosṭātewos</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>.
                            Both men have a small hand <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d20">
                           <locus target="#24r">Fol. 24r</locus>
                            <desc>
                              <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>:
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6298Libanos">Libānos</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8491Samuel">Sāmuʾel of Wāldǝbbā</persName>.
                                Both men have a small hand <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> and perform a <term key="gestureblessing" ana="#gestureblessing"/>.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d21">
                           <locus target="#25r">Fol. 25r</locus>
                            <desc>
                              <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>:
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1246AbibBu">Bulā</persName> and a second saint.
                                Both men have a small hand <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> and perform a <term key="gestureblessing" ana="#gestureblessing"/>.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
    
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d22">
                           <locus target="#26r">Fol. 26r</locus>
                            <desc>
                              <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>:
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName> as lord over the animals. He is in an <term key="gestureorans" ana="#gestureorans">orans pose</term> and is flanked by lions.</desc>
                        </decoNote>
                     </decoDesc>
                        
                        
